@ericl after looking at this a bit more, I think the "duplicated" object IDs are not a real phenomenon. In particular, the appearance of duplicate object IDs occurs when you go through the `else` branch of the statement

```python
        if pending:
            ready, pending = ray.wait(
                pending, num_returns=min(1, len(pending)), timeout=10)
        else:
            time.sleep(.01)
```

Because then the `ready` set gets reused from one iteration to the next.

